CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 21, 1955, pg. 17 reads: " "Everything's All Right"...is the assurance the Rev. Amos Brackeen (second from left) is giving to Henry Ryan (second from right), Democratic candidate for alderman in the Thirteenth Ward. Listening with interest are Mrs. Ismay Harris, Mrs. Martha Vannall and Mrs. Mary Epson.  Ryan lost to Sara Kirk. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. Ismay Harris, Rev. Amos Brackeen, Martha Vannall, Henry Ryan, and Mary Epson standing on residential street in front of automobiles and houses, during 1955 primary elections
